                "Accelerator Laboratory of Florida State University."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The beam was delivered to a natural self-supporting",
                "vanadium target of thickness 610 microg/cm2 that was",
                "mounted in the target chamber of spectrograph. The",
                "natural abundance of 51V is 99.75%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Super-Enge Split-Pole Spectrograph (SE-",
                "SPS), which accepted a solid angle of 2.3 msr, was",
                "rotated from scattering angles of 15 to 50 degree at",
                "increments of 5 degree to measure angular",
                "distributions of protons from the 51V(d,p)52V",
                "reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The proton momentum spectra were collected at",
                "different scattering angles and magnetic field",
                "settings. The proton yields corresponding to each",
                "state in 52V were used to produce the measured proton",
                "angular distributions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The absolute cross sections were",
                "determined to be accurate within an uncertainty of",
                "15%, with contributions from uncertainties in charge",
                "integration, target thickness and solid angle."
              ]
            }
